{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Changing canvas size and observing the effect on its coordinate system:</p>\n<data type='yaml'>\ntype: algorithmx-example\ncode:\n  js: |\n    canvas.size([300, 150])\n    \n    canvas.node(1).add().pos(['-cx + 35', 'cy - 35']).fixed(true)\n    canvas.node(2).add().pos(['cx - 35', 'cy - 35']).fixed(true)\n    canvas.node(3).add().pos(['-cx + 35', '-cy + 35']).fixed(true)\n    canvas.node(4).add().pos(['cx - 35', '-cy + 35']).fixed(true)\n    canvas.edges([[1, 2], [2, 4], [4, 3], [3, 1]]).add()\n    \n    canvas.node('c').add()\n      .shape('rect')\n      .size([50, 12])\n      .pos([0, 0])\n      .label().text('Center (0, 0)')\n  python: |\n    canvas.size((300, 150))\n    \n    canvas.node(1).add().pos(('-cx + 35', 'cy - 35')).fixed(True)\n    canvas.node(2).add().pos(('cx - 35', 'cy - 35')).fixed(True)\n    canvas.node(3).add().pos(('-cx + 35', '-cy + 35')).fixed(True)\n    canvas.node(4).add().pos(('cx - 35', '-cy + 35')).fixed(True)\n    canvas.edges([[1, 2], [2, 4], [4, 3], [3, 1]]).add()\n    \n    canvas.node('c').add() \\\n      .shape('rect') \\\n      .size([50, 12]) \\\n      .pos([0, 0]) \\\n      .label().text('Center (0, 0)')\n</data>\n<p>Note that, in this case, the actual size of the canvas is predetermined.</p>","fields":{"slug":"/api/CanvasSelection/size/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Size","docs":["CanvasSelection.size"]}},"file":{"childJson":{"entries":[{"type":"folder","name":"Selection","path":"Selection/"},{"type":"folder","name":"CanvasSelection","path":"CanvasSelection/"},{"type":"folder","name":"NodeSelection","path":"NodeSelection/"},{"type":"folder","name":"EdgeSelection","path":"EdgeSelection/"},{"type":"folder","name":"LabelSelection","path":"LabelSelection/"}]}},"allMarkdownRemark":{"edges":[{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/api/CanvasSelection/edgelengths/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Edge Lengths"}}},{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/api/CanvasSelection/panZoom/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Pan & Zoom"}}},{"node":{"f